        "text": "The document page contains two tables and a section discussing financial transmission rights.\n\n**Table A-5: TCC Cost by Path**\n- Displays the Transmission Congestion Contract (TCC) costs for various paths during the Winter 2020/21 and Summer 2021 capability periods.\n- Costs are listed for different paths such as WEST, GENESE, CENTRAL, and others, with a total cost of $253.\n\n**Table A-6: TCC Profit by Path**\n- Shows the TCC profits for the same paths and periods.\n- Profits are calculated similarly, with a total profit of $66.\n\n**Section J: Potential Design of Financial Transmission Rights for PAR Operation**\n- Discusses creating a financial right to compensate ConEd if lines between NYC and Long Island are scheduled efficiently.\n- The financial right should compensate based on marginal production cost savings and ensure no uplift for NYISO customers.\n- The concept emphasizes that the right should reflect the marginal cost of relieving congestion, aligning with how generators and customers are charged.",
