      {
        "id": "94b5a1ce-f64e-4a62-afab-64300e5604df",
        "score": 0.5197011,
        "text": "The document outlines the process for monthly certification of Unforced Capacity (UCAP) by Installed Capacity Suppliers to the New York Independent System Operator (NYISO). Suppliers must certify that their UCAP is not already committed to other requirements by a specified deadline, as detailed in the ICAP Event Calendar. Suppliers with rights to Unforced Deliverability Rights (UDRs) from external areas must confirm non-use for self-supply by the May certification deadline. Suppliers with derated capacity must demonstrate they have procured additional UCAP to cover any shortfall.\n\nIf a supplier sells UCAP, they remain responsible for its certification unless a bilateral agreement or auction covers it. If UCAP includes New Special Case Resources, the original seller retains certification responsibility. If a bilateral transaction is unconfirmed, the responsibility remains with the supplier who submitted it.",
        "metadata": {
