        "text": "The document outlines the process for submitting cost components related to Regulation Movement to the NYISO. It emphasizes the need for both quantitative and qualitative data from Market Participants. Quantitative estimates should follow a specific framework:\n\n1. **Thermal Losses**: \n   - Report additional mmBTUs consumed during regulation for one hour.\n   - Calculate the percentage increase in fuel consumption using a ratio of additional mmBTUs consumed during regulation to total mmBTUs consumed when not on regulation.\n\n2. **Maintenance Costs**:\n   - Provide the dollar amount of additional maintenance costs per hour of regulation.\n   - Calculate the percentage increase in maintenance costs by comparing additional costs during regulation to costs when not on regulation.\n\nThe NYISO will calculate Regulation Movement costs per MW-hr using:\n- Burdened fuel cost information for thermal losses.\n- Heat rate data for thermal losses.",
